Use of American Airlines, Inc.'s Flight Status Notification service is subject to all terms and conditions of the American Airlines Privacy Policy.
Due to privacy considerations, if you reside outside of the 50 United States, Puerto Rico, and the U.S. Virgin Islands, you may not designate anyone other than yourself as the recipient for the notification.
"Supported Carriers:" Our participating carriers include (but not limited to) AT&T, Sprint, Verizon Wireless, U.S. Cellular® and T-Mobile®.
Flight status updates can be sent to a mobile device, cell phone, home or business phone, or email account. Flight status notifications are sent as a text, voice, or email message, depending on your selection. Text messages are sent to your mobile device via SMS (Short Message Service). For email notification, your mobile device must have internet email browsing capability. For voice message notifications, the recipient must have a 10-digit mobile number from the U.S., Canada, Puerto Rico, or U.S. Virgin Islands. For text message notifications, the recipient must have a 10-digit mobile number from the U.S. or Canada. Standard Text and Voice Messaging Rates May Apply. Due to privacy laws, if you reside outside of the 50 United States, Puerto Rico, and the U.S. Virgin Islands, you may not designate anyone other than yourself as the recipient for the notification."
